<body>
	<div class="container">
			<div class="notice"></div>
			<div class="popup-window">
				<div id="about">
					<p>
						<span>About</span>
						<br />This site is designed to help you quickly identify businesses and other food establishments that have had critical and non critical issues in the last 3 years (2010-2012). This map's sole purpose is to disseminate raw data provided to us by the Nebraska Department of Agriculture.
						<br /><br />
						<i>Use this information at your own risk.</i>
						<br /><br />
						Created by Ross Nelson, Dustin Lipskey, and other contributors. <a href="https://github.com/rnelson/ne_state_restaurant_inspections">View on Github</a>. Made in coopration with <a href="http://opennebraska.io">Open Nebraska</a>.
					</p>
				</div>
				<div id="how">
					<p>
						<span>How To Use</span>
						<br />You may click on any point that loads on the map, showing you a snapshot of the location. You can link to that specific result, or you may also look at any other properties owned by that property owner.
						<br /><br />
						You can search by restaurant or location. For example a query like "<b>14th and Old Cheney</b>" will center the map on the intersection of 14th and Old Cheney Rd in Lincoln, NE. <br /><br /><b><i>Best practices recommend that you include the city name at all costs just to ensure accuracy.</i></b>
						<br /><br />
						When clicking "Inspection Details" you can now see when inspections were done by State Inspectors and their individual results and can share these results on social media (Twitter and Facebook).
					</p>
				</div>
				<div id="soon">
					<p>
						<span>Coming Soon</span>
						<br />
						<ul>
							<li>Social network integration, such as Yelp! and Foursquare</li>
							<li>User Interface / Experience improvements.</li>
							<li>More data from sources like
								<ul>
									<li>County inspections</li>
									<li>City inspections</li>
									<li>Neighboring states</li>
								</ul>
							</li>
						</ul>
					</p>
				</div>
				<a class="link-close">close</a>
				<div style="clear:both;">&nbsp;</div>
			</div>
		<div class="heading">
			<div class="heading-header">
				<a href="/">Nebraska Food Inspections</a>
			</div>
			<div class="home">
				<img src="/img/home.png" />
			</div>
			<div class="heading-header-links">
				<a class="popup link-about">about</a> | <a class="popup link-how">how to use</a> | <a class="popup link-soon">coming soon</a>
			</div>
			<div class="search-box">
				<a href="" class="share-link">Share</a>
				<form id="form">
					<input type="text" id="search" name="search" placeholder="Find restaurant or location..." />
					<input type="submit" id="searchbutton" value="" />
				</form>
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="map">
			<div id="map"></div>
		</div>
	</div>
